descriptions: High-altitude multi-sensor dataset collected using ANYmal D with Boxi sensor suite at Jungfraujoch (3580 m), covering 15 deployments across varied environments (outdoor snow/ice, glacier interiors, tunnels, industrial spaces) with synchronized LiDAR, camera, IMU, GNSS, and ground-truth data. Designed to assist research in localization, mapping, and control for legged robots in extreme conditions. Planned for public release with calibration files and environmental logs.
Frey, J. et al. “Boxi: Design Decisions in the Context of Algorithmic Performance for Robotics”. RSS (2025). Under review.
